The organisation was brought to life for the avoidance of the marginalisation by young people without professional training.
The first 25 years of the social aid organisation of Trinijove have led to important results: This quarter century 6000 became has young, from the social exclusion threatened people supported to find a way out from her difficult situation.
There there come more than hundred jobs created for this social group.
Yesterday on the occasion of the anniversary balance was struck in an event in the former work buildings by Fabra i Coats in which more than 300 people took part.
Trinijove was brought to life in 1986 in the town quarter Trinitat Vella with the aim to help young people with low education state, without work, with the drug problems which were threatened by the risk of the Marginalität.
Numerous persons responsible of facilities and institutions who have worked together during these 25 years with the association took part in the yesterday's celebration in Sant Andreu.
The participation of political representatives of different directions at election campaign times booked the impartiality of the work performed by Trinijove.
Except the president of the Generalitat (parliament of the autonomous region Catalonia), Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol took part in the festivities the former socialist minister of education Ernest Maragall and the former mayor and presently left green town council of Ricard Goma.
The big hall of Fabra i Coats also visited the present katalonische minister for social and family, Josep Lluís Cleries, and the general manager of the social work of the savings bank of La Caixa, Jaume Lanaspa.
Mas stressed that Trinijove was brought to life in very difficult times and that the today's times are not complicated less. But he added that the work performed till present is "a good basis".
For the president of the Generalitat Trinijove is a model which knows how to fight against difficult circumstances and gives people in difficulties to hope.
"The economic crisis is for the association and the work which he performs, nothing new", he explained.
